ers, large-scale nurseries, occasionally Australian agricultural suppliers.", "sort_order": 8}, {"name": "Melissa officinalis ''Mandarina''", "slug": "melissa-officinalis-mandarina", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Selected cultivar with unique citrus profile", "traits": "40-70cm height, lower spreading growth habit than standard, broader stance", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good, spreading habit provides abundant foliage", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Specialty herb nurseries UK (First Tunnels), rare in Australia, occasional imports, herb collectors.", "sort_order": 9}, {"name": "Melissa officinalis ''Binsuga''", "slug": "melissa-officinalis-binsuga", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Modern selection bred for high essential oil content", "traits": "60-90cm height, very vigorous bushy growth, robust structure", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Excellent, especially vigorous growth for tea production", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "European herb seed companies, specialty suppliers, rare in Australia, online international herb seed catalogs.", "sort_order": 10}, {"name": "Melissa officinalis (Common/Standard)", "slug": "melissa-officinalis-common-standard", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Mediterranean Basin, South-central Europe, Central Asia, Iran. Cultivated since 16th century.", "traits": "Bushy upright growth 50-90cm, green heart-shaped leaves with scalloped edges, heavily veined and hairy texture, square stems", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "High productivity, multiple harvests per season, vigorous regrowth after cutting", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "OrganicBazar.net (India-wide delivery), The Affordable Organic Store (online India), Nurserylive.com (pan-India), Cleantech Mart, Kerala local nurseries in Kottayam and Ernakulam districts, herbal farms in Idukki.", "sort_order": 0}, 