sh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Abundant flowering over long season", "growing_notes": "INDIGENOUS TO KERALA. Regarded as one of most sacred trees of India and tropical Asia. Flowers used in religious ceremonies, temple offerings, garlands. Essential oil extracted for perfume industry. Thrives in Kerala''s tropical monsoon climate - ideal heat, humidity, and rainfall. Can be grown in containers with pruning. Seeds dispersed by birds. Known locally as Sampangi in South India.", "availability": "Widely cultivated - Local Kerala nurseries, Plantshub India, Indian garden centers, temple gardens. Seeds and plants readily available.", "sort_order": 0}, {"name": "Magnolia × alba (White Champaka, Pak-Lan) 🧬 🏆", "slug": "magnolia-alba-white-champaka-pak-lan", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Cultivated origin (M. champaca × M. montana hybrid), Southeast Asia and China, introduced to Taiwan 17th century. Cultivated for centuries", "traits": "Medium-sized evergreen tree to 30m, smooth silvery-grey bark, elliptical leaves 10-35cm × 4-11cm", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Heavy flowering over extended season", "growing_notes": "CULTURALLY SIGNIFICANT IN KERALA. White version of champaca. Flowers woven into garlands for traditional ceremonies, weddings, religious offerings in Indonesia and Thailand. Essential oil extracted for perfume industry (200+ patents). Known as ''Bai Yu Lan'' (white-jade flower) in China. Thrives perfectly in Kerala''s tropical monsoon climate. Sterile hybrid propagated vegetatively. Popular street tree.", "availability": "Widely available - Kerala nurseries, Indian garden centers, flower markets during season", "sort_order": 1}, {"name": "Golden Magnolia (Simhachalam Sampenga) 🌱", "slug": "golden-magnolia-simhachalam-sampenga", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India, associated with Simhachalam temple near Vishakhapatnam", "traits": "Small to medium evergreen tree", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "4-6 flowers produced daily during season", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 2}, {"name": "Green Magnolia (Aaku Sampenga/Manoranjitam) 🌱", "slug": "green-magnolia-aaku-sampenga-manoranjitam", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India, traditional cultivation", "traits": "Small to medium evergreen tree, can grow to 3m (10 feet)", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Regular flowering", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "White Sampangi (Teega Sampangi) 🌱", "slug": "white-sampangi-teega-sampangi", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India, traditional variety", "traits": "Small evergreen tree or large shrub", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Flowering when established", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Magnolia doltsopa (Sweet Michelia, Temple Tree) 🌱", "slug": "magnolia-doltsopa-sweet-michelia-temple-tree", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Eastern Himalayas, Meghalaya subtropical forests (India), native 1500-2400m elevation", "traits": "Large shrub to tree 20-30m, leathery dark-green leaves 6-17cm length", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good winter flowering", "growing_notes": "NATIVE TO INDIA including Meghalaya. Growing in popularity as street tree in coastal California. Prefers higher elevations (1500-2400m) but can adapt to Kerala''s lower elevation tropical climate with adequate moisture. Best in areas with mean annual rainfall 3000-4000mm (Kerala receives heavy monsoon). Tolerates 5-45°C. Wood harvested from wild.", "availability": "Limited in Kerala lowlands, better for hill stations, Indian botanical gardens", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Magnolia nilagirica (Nilgiri Magnolia) 🌱 🏆", "slug": "magnolia-nilagirica-nilgiri-magnolia", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "ENDEMIC