mate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "China, cultivated for centuries", "traits": "Compact evergreen shrub 3-5m, small glossy green leaves, dense bushy habit", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Prolific flowering over long season", "growing_notes": "EXCELLENT FOR KERALA. Thrives in tropical to subtropical climates. Perfect for Kerala''s monsoon conditions - tolerates high heat and humidity. Also popular as houseplant. Can be grown in containers. Flowers covered with velvet-like hairs. ''Port Wine'' cultivar has deeper rose-maroon flowers. Isoamyl alcohol provides banana scent. Slow-growing, low-maintenance.", "availability": "Available through specialty tropical plant importers to India, may require sourcing from international suppliers", "sort_order": 9}, {"name": "M. figo var. crassipes", "slug": "m-figo-var-crassipes", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "China", "traits": "Larger robust variety, can reach 5m+", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Heavy flowering", "growing_notes": "More vigorous than standard figo. Excellent for Kerala''s tropical monsoon climate. Used in breeding. Heat and humidity tolerant. Flowers covered with velvet-like hairs.", "availability": "Specialty tropical plant suppliers, international nurseries", "sort_order": 10}, {"name": "Magnolia rajaniana (Peacock Magnolia, Champa Khao)", "slug": "magnolia-rajaniana-peacock-magnolia-champa-khao", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Southeast Asia, variety of M. champaca", "traits": "Evergreen tree", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good flowering", "growing_notes": "Known as Champee Si Nuan or Magnolia Ivory. Thrives in tropical climates like Kerala. Similar care to champaca.", "availability": "Limited, specialty tropical plant collectors", "sort_order": 11}, {"name": "Magnolia coco (Dwarf Magnolia, Coconut Magnolia)", "slug": "magnolia-coco-dwarf-magnolia-coconut-magnolia", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Southeast Asia (Cempaka Telur, Cempaka Gondok)", "traits": "Dwarf/compact form magnolia", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Regular flowering", "growing_notes": "Compact form suitable for smaller Kerala gardens. Tropical climate adapted. Also known as Liriodendron coco, Magnolia pumila.", "availability": "Rare, specialty tropical plant collectors", "sort_order": 12}, {"name": "Little Gem", "slug": "little-gem", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Monrovia Nursery, USA, mid-20th century", "traits": "Dwarf form 3-4m tall, narrow upright habit, glossy green leaves with rusty undersides", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Continuous bloomer late spring through summer", "growing_notes": "Can be adapted to Kerala with consistent water during monsoon and protection from extreme midday heat. Suitable for containers. Slow-growing. Best in partial shade in Kerala conditions.", "availability": "Plantshub India, may require special order/import", "sort_order": 13}, {"name": "Teddy Bear", "slug": "teddy-bear", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Australia, late 20th century", "traits": "Compact pyramidal 4-5m, dense branching, glossy dark green leaves with rusty-brown undersides", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Prolific bloomer", "growing_notes": "Heat and humidity tolerant. Can adapt to Kerala''s tropical monsoon climate with adequate water and some afternoon shade. Popular worldwide in subtropical to tropical zones.", "availability": "May be available through Plantshub India or specialty importers", "sort_order": 14}, {"name": "D.D. Blanchard", "slug": "d-d-blanchard", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "North Carolina, USA", "traits": "Large tree 15-18m, pyramidal, very dark glossy leaves with rusty-orange undersides", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good flowering", "growing_notes": "Tolerates sub